countryname: The former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia

iso_code: * Lower and Upper refer to the lower bound and upper bound of 90% uncertainty intervals
U5MR is the under-five mortlality rate (Probability of dying between birth and exactly 5 years of age, expressed per 1,000 live births)
IMR is the infant mortality rate (Probability of dying between birth and exactly 1 year of age, expressed per 1,000 live births)
NMR is the neonatal mortality rate (Probability of dying in the ﬁrst 28 days of life, expressed per 1,000 live births)
